    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "c98dd91a_250adcd2",
        "filename": "cipd/appengine/impl/repo/repo.go",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 80,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-03-22T19:08:29Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "FWIU, the shorter the prefix, the more restricted its ACLs are. E.g. only administrators group owns root. The longer the prefix, the broader group can own it.\n\ni find the following a bit strange:\n\nGiven a random user U\n- if U doesn\u0027t own any prefixes, U can\u0027t see metadata of any prefix\n- if admins give U permissions for prefix a/b/c/d/e/f, which is super specific and it is OK for U to own it, suddenly U can see metadata of all prefixes of a/b/c/d/e/f. This is somewhat backwards to how inheritance works in other places. Normally, if you own a prefix, you can see its descendants, NOT ancestors.\n\nWhat do you think about this?\ndid you consider to maybe return metadata only of prefixes that the requester owns?\n\non the other hand, I admit that U may want to know how can fetch their packages.\n\nif you knew all this already, maybe document it somewhere",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 76,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 80,
        "endChar": 4
      },
      "revId": "ff3bbdd0463551b4e4687b38b812b577f30c48eb",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "866023ca_54aba671",
        "filename": "cipd/appengine/impl/repo/repo.go",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 80,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-03-23T00:49:40Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think it\u0027s important to let owners know who precisely can fetch their packages. I\u0027ll document this behavior in repo.proto in https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/infra/luci/luci-go/+/974881\n\nNote I also consider later adding separate role METADATA_READER and grant it to all googlers at the root (or somewhere up top), so non-owners can also see metadata (but not actual package data). This is important to let people know who should they ping or to what group should they apply if they want to get access to some prefix.",
      "parentUuid": "c98dd91a_250adcd2",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 76,
